  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 18:42 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] V5a Patch Finalized + 19h Pre-Trade Analysis\n\n**Task:** Build the V5a patch for Apr 6 deploy + analyze 19h trade probability.\n\n**19h Trade Probability: LOW (~15%)**\n- Bias at 18:38-18:43: +12 to +84 (POSITIVE \u2014 BTC rallying)\n- YES-only strategy requires NEGATIVE bias\n- Even if regime clears from TREND 5/6 to RANGE, positive bias = NO YES trades\n- BTC at $67,749 \u2014 would need to pull back $600+ to generate negative bias\n- Shadow trade tracker will log what WOULD have traded\n\n**V5a Patch \u2014 COMPLETE:**\nTwo-line change to `trading_bot.py`:\n1. `self.bias_threshold = 45.0` (was 25.0)\n2. Remove dead zone filter at 35-45 (now redundant, threshold covers it)\n\nThe dead zone was already blocking 35-45. V5a simply extends that to 25-45 in a clean single setting.\n\n**Deploy checklist:**\n- \u2705 Patch written (`patches/v5a-min-bias-45.patch.md`)\n- \u2705 Zombie bug fixed, single process stable\n- \u23f3 5 stable days (Apr 1-5)\n- \u23f3 Indicator logging confirmed\n\n**Shadow trading analysis (18:30-18:45 UTC):**\n- Bias +66 to +84 = strong bullish PM signal\n- If we traded NO (which we don't): would have caught the BTC rally\n- But V3.2 prevents NO trades (40% WR) \u2014 CORRECT\n- The \"missed\" NO trades here are the ones we correctly skip\n\n**Next P2:** Post-19h analysis at 19:15 UTC \u2014 did bot trade? Check indicator logging.\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 18:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] Pre-19h Intel: Alternation Pattern BROKE, BTC Rally Organic\n\n**Task:** Pre-19h window intelligence gathering and regime forecast.\n\n**BTC CASCADE Alternation Pattern UPDATE:**\n```\n13:50 SHORT_LIQ \u2192 14:55 LONG_LIQ \u2192 15:15 SHORT_LIQ \u2192 16:45 SHORT_LIQ \u2192 17:15 SHORT_LIQ\n```\nThe alternation broke at 16:45 \u2014 three consecutive SHORT_LIQ cascades. This means the BTC rally is a sustained short squeeze, not a whipsaw. BTC: $66,200 \u2192 $67,777 (+2.4% in 9h).\n\n**New liq events (16:00-17:40):**\n- BTC: 2 CASCADE SHORT_LIQ ($31.7M) \u2014 shorts getting destroyed\n- SOL: 1 CASCADE SHORT_LIQ \u2192 1 CASCADE LONG_LIQ \u2192 1 LIQ LONG_LIQ ($15.6M) \u2014 SOL flipped\n\n**Funding rates (HL):** All balanced/slightly negative. The rally is organic spot buying, not leverage-driven. This makes it more sustainable but also means no funding arb opportunity.\n\n**19h Window Forecast:**\n- Regime: TREND 5/6 \u2192 **likely BLOCKED**\n- BTC at $67,777 still rallying \u2192 regime may worsen to STRONG_TREND\n- For bot to trade: need BTC pullback \u2192 lower regime \u2192 negative bias \u2192 YES setup\n- Probability of 19h trade: **~25%** (need regime drop from 5/6 to \u22643/6 in 52 min)\n\n**HL positions:** BTC +$1.38, ETH +$0.11, SOL -$0.05. Net +$1.44. All 3 LONGs benefiting from the rally.\n\n**Copy signal:** neutral@2% \u2014 no useful information.\n\n**Decision:** No pre-emptive action. Monitor regime at 19:00 sharp. If still TREND/STRONG_TREND, bot correctly blocks. The regime filter has saved us $50+ today by avoiding trades during this volatile trending day.\n\n**Next P1:** Post-19h analysis \u2014",
